p.foreignPolicy:
It would be in the power of the maritime nations,
                    availing themselves of our universal impotence, to prescribe the conditions of
                    our political existence;

p.federalism:
It can be conducted upon much better terms with a large
                    number of materials of a given value than with a small number of materials of
                    the same value;

It may perhaps be replied to this, that whether the States
                    are united or disunited, there would still be an intimate intercourse between
                    them which would answer the same ends;
